SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION  

  Chemical signals act as the main reproductive barrier between sister and mimetic  Heliconius  butterflies   

 Gonz&aacute;lez-Rojas, M.F. 1 , Darragh, K. 2 , Robles, J 3 ., Linares, M. 1 , Schulz, S 4 ., McMillan, W.O 5 ., Jiggins, C.D 2 ., Pardo-Diaz, C 1 ., Salazar, C 1 . 

 &nbsp; 

 1. GC/MS raw data&nbsp; 

 2. Behavioural experiments dataset (raw data) 

  3. Heliconius  images and landmark coordinates ( H. timareta florencia  and  H. melpomene malleti ) for colour pattern comparison for each wing element analysed:&nbsp; 

 - Yellow patch on the dorsal and ventral forewing 

 - Dennis on the dorsal and ventral forewing 

 - Ray on the dorsal and ventral hindwing 

 &nbsp;

